headline: Maplebear Stock Sees Relative Strength Rating Rise To 83
summary: One important metric to look for in a stock is an 80 or higher Relative Strength Rating.  Maplebear stock just hit that mark, with a jump from 77 to 83 Thursday.  Over 100 years of market history shows that the top-performing stocks typically have an 80 or higher RS Rating in the early stages of their moves.
